{
  "texts": [
    "Each expert independently rated the topics on a scale of one to five, with 5 indicating the highest level of coherence, meaning that the topic was clearly relevant, distinct, and understandable.",
    "A score of 1, on the other hand, indicated that the topic required further refinement, either because it was too broad, had overlapping themes, or was difficult to interpret.",
    "After completing their ratings, the experts met to discuss their scores and address any differences.",
    "During these discussions, they reviewed specific keywords and representative articles, ensuring that each topic accurately reflected a distinct theme.",
    "If there were any inconsistencies in the scores, they worked together to either adjust the topic or find a common understanding."
  ]
}